---

<VizLayout
  {title}
  currentPath="/module1/viz-1-2-bayes"
  pageCss="/assets/css/pages/viz-1-2-bayes.css"
>
  <div class="gd-breadcrumb">
    <a href="/index.html">Home</a><span>›</span>
    <a href="/module1.html">Module 1</a><span>›</span>
    1.2 Conditional Probability &amp; Bayes' Theorem
  </div>
  <a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module1.html">← Module 1 Overview</a>

  <div class="gd-viz-header">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--subject">Module 1 · P&amp;S</span>
      <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--pyq">2024 Q58 · 2025 Q31 · 2026 Q57</span>
    </div>
    <h1 id="top">Conditional Probability &amp; Bayes' Theorem</h1>
    <p>
      Appears every GATE DA paper — almost always as a 2-mark NAT. Master the
      playbook: prior × likelihood ÷ total probability. Drag the sliders to see
      why base rate matters more than sensitivity.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     THEORY 1 — CONDITIONAL PROBABILITY
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="theory">Conditional Probability</h2>

  <p>
    When event $B$ has occurred, the sample space shrinks to $B$. Conditional
    probability asks: within $B$, what fraction also satisfies $A$?
  </p>

  <div class="gd-formula-panel">
    <div class="gd-formula-label">Definition</div>
    <div class="gd-formula">
      $$P(A \mid B) = \frac&#123;P(A \cap B)&#125;&#123;P(B)&#125;, \quad P(B) >
      0$$
    </div>
  </div>

  <p style="color:var(--gd-text-1);font-size:15px;margin-bottom:18px;">
    Rearranging gives the <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);"
      >multiplication rule:</strong
    > $P(A \cap B) = P(A \mid B) \cdot P(B)$. For a chain of draws without replacement:
    $P(A_1 \cap A_2 \cap \cdots \cap A_n) = P(A_1) \cdot P(A_2 \mid A_1) \cdot P(A_3
    \mid A_1, A_2) \cdots$
  </p>

  <h3 id="independence">Independence</h3>

  <p>
    $A$ and $B$ are <strong>independent</strong> iff knowing one gives no information
    about the other. All three conditions are equivalent:
  </p>

  <div class="rules-grid">
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card__label">Independence — three equivalent tests</div>
      <div class="gd-formula">$$P(A \cap B) = P(A) \cdot P(B)$$</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin:8px 0 0;">
        Equivalently: $P(A \mid B) = P(A)$, or $P(B \mid A) = P(B)$. Any one
        implies all three.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rule-card">
      <div class="rule-card__label">Mutually exclusive ≠ independent</div>
      <div class="gd-formula">
        $$A \cap B = \emptyset \;\Longrightarrow\; \text&#123;dependent&#125;$$
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin:8px 0 0;">
        If $P(A), P(B) > 0$: ME gives $P(A \cap B) = 0 \ne P(A)P(B)$. They
        cannot both happen, so they are maximally dependent.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--insight">
      <span class="gd-insight__title"
        >Intuition: conditional = new sample space</span
      >
      $P(A \mid B)$ = (cell A∩B) ÷ (row total B) in a contingency table. The denominator
      is the total probability of $B$, not the entire sample space.
    </div>
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--warn">
      <span class="gd-insight__title"
        >Classic GATE trap — ME implies dependent</span
      >
      Students confuse "can't happen together" with "don't influence each other."
      Mutually exclusive events with positive probability are in fact <em
        >dependent</em
      > — knowing $A$ happened tells you $B$ didn't. GATE 2024 Q12 tested this directly.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     VIZ 1 — PROBABILITY SQUARE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="viz1">Interactive: The Probability Square</h2>

  <div class="gd-formula-panel gd-formula-panel--split">
    <div>
      <div class="gd-formula-label">Bayes' Theorem</div>
      <div class="gd-formula">
        $$P(H \mid E) = \frac&#123;P(E \mid H)\,P(H)&#125;&#123;P(E \mid
        H)\,P(H) + P(E \mid \neg H)\,P(\neg H)&#125;$$
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="gd-formula-label">Current values</div>
      <div class="gd-formula-live" id="formula-live-1">—</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-chart" style="position:relative;">
    <div class="gd-chart__title">
      1×1 square = entire sample space. Blue corner = P(H ∩ E) = posterior
      numerator. Hover regions for values.
    </div>
    <div id="bayes-square"></div>
    <div class="gd-tooltip" id="sq-tooltip"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-controls">
    <div class="gd-controls__title">Parameters</div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">P(H)</span> Prior probability of hypothesis
        H</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="ph-val">0.30</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="ph"
        min="0.01"
        max="0.99"
        step="0.01"
        value="0.30"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">P(E|H)</span> Likelihood — evidence given H
        true</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="peh-val">0.90</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="peh"
        min="0.01"
        max="0.99"
        step="0.01"
        value="0.90"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">P(E|¬H)</span> False alarm rate — evidence
        given H false</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="penh-val">0.20</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="penh"
        min="0.01"
        max="0.99"
        step="0.01"
        value="0.20"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--active" id="ins-posterior">
      Posterior: —
    </div>
    <div class="gd-insight" id="ins-pe">P(E): —</div>
    <div class="gd-insight" id="ins-ratio">Likelihood ratio: —</div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     THEORY 2 — LAW OF TOTAL PROBABILITY
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="total-prob">Law of Total Probability</h2>

  <p>
    If $B_1, \ldots, B_n$ <strong>partition</strong> the sample space (disjoint and
    exhaustive), then for any event $A$:
  </p>

  <div class="gd-formula-panel">
    <div class="gd-formula-label">Law of Total Probability</div>
    <div class="gd-formula">
      $$P(A) = \sum_&#123;i=1&#125;^n P(A \mid B_i)\,P(B_i)$$
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--insight">
      <span class="gd-insight__title">This is the Bayes denominator</span>
      Every Bayes calculation requires $P(E)$ in the denominator. That is computed
      by the law of total probability — averaging likelihoods weighted by priors.
      The probability tree (Viz 3) shows each branch contributing one term.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     THEORY 3 — BAYES' THEOREM
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="bayes">Bayes' Theorem</h2>

  <p>
    Bayes converts $P(\text&#123;evidence&#125; \mid \text&#123;cause&#125;)$
    into $P(\text&#123;cause&#125; \mid \text&#123;evidence&#125;)$ — reversing
    the conditional. This is the key operation in every Bayesian inference
    problem:
  </p>

  <div class="gd-formula-panel">
    <div class="gd-formula-label">General form</div>
    <div class="gd-formula">
      $$P(B_k \mid A) = \frac&#123;P(A \mid B_k)\cdot
      P(B_k)&#125;&#123;\displaystyle\sum_j P(A \mid B_j)\cdot P(B_j)&#125;$$
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bayes-terms">
    <div class="bayes-term">
      <div class="bayes-term__sym">$P(B_k)$</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__name">Prior</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__desc">Belief before evidence</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bayes-term">
      <div class="bayes-term__sym">$P(A \mid B_k)$</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__name">Likelihood</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__desc">How well $B_k$ explains evidence $A$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bayes-term">
      <div class="bayes-term__sym">$\sum_j P(A \mid B_j)P(B_j)$</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__name">Evidence</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__desc">Total probability of observation</div>
    </div>
    <div class="bayes-term bayes-term--posterior">
      <div class="bayes-term__sym">$P(B_k \mid A)$</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__name">Posterior</div>
      <div class="bayes-term__desc">Updated belief after seeing $A$</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--insight">
      <span class="gd-insight__title"
        >The Bayes playbook — 5 steps every time</span
      >
      1. Name hypotheses $B_i$ (partition) and evidence $A$. &nbsp; 2. Write priors
      $P(B_i)$. &nbsp; 3. Write likelihoods $P(A \mid B_i)$. &nbsp; 4. Total probability:
      $P(A) = \sum P(A \mid B_i)P(B_i)$. &nbsp; 5. Bayes: numerator $P(A \mid B_k)P(B_k)$
      divided by $P(A)$.
    </div>
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--warn">
      <span class="gd-insight__title"
        >Base rate neglect — the examiner's favourite</span
      >
      Even a 99%-sensitive test gives a low posterior when prevalence is 0.1%. The
      prior $P(\text&#123;disease&#125;)$ dominates the denominator. The medical test
      visualization below makes this concrete.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     VIZ 2 — MEDICAL TEST
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="viz2">Interactive: Medical Test — Base Rate Effect</h2>

  <p style="color:var(--gd-text-1);margin-bottom:16px;font-size:15px;">
    Set prevalence to 0.1% and sensitivity to 99% — watch P(Disease | Test+)
    collapse. This is the <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);"
      >base rate fallacy</strong
    > that GATE 2026 Q57 tested.
  </p>

  <div class="gd-chart">
    <div class="gd-chart__title">
      Out of 10 000 people — bar shows true positives (blue) vs false positives
      (amber)
    </div>
    <div id="medical-bars"></div>
  </div>

  <div id="medical-grid">
    <div class="medical-cell">
      <div class="medical-cell__label">True Positives (TP)</div>
      <div class="medical-cell__val" id="med-tp">—</div>
    </div>
    <div class="medical-cell">
      <div class="medical-cell__label">False Positives (FP)</div>
      <div class="medical-cell__val" id="med-fp">—</div>
    </div>
    <div class="medical-cell">
      <div class="medical-cell__label">Test+ Total</div>
      <div class="medical-cell__val" id="med-total-pos">—</div>
    </div>
    <div class="medical-cell medical-cell--highlight">
      <div class="medical-cell__label">P(Disease | Test+)</div>
      <div class="medical-cell__val" id="med-posterior">—</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-controls" style="margin-top:16px;">
    <div class="gd-controls__title">Test parameters</div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">prev</span> Disease prevalence in population</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="prev-val">0.1%</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="prevalence"
        min="0.0001"
        max="0.5"
        step="0.0001"
        value="0.001"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">sens</span> Sensitivity P(Test+ | Disease)</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="sens-val">0.99</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="sensitivity"
        min="0.50"
        max="0.999"
        step="0.001"
        value="0.99"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control">
      <label class="gd-control__label"
        ><span class="gd-control__sym">spec</span> Specificity P(Test− | No disease)</label
      >
      <span class="gd-control__value" id="spec-val">0.95</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-control--full">
      <input
        class="gd-control__slider"
        type="range"
        id="specificity"
        min="0.50"
        max="0.999"
        step="0.001"
        value="0.95"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-insights">
    <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--warn" id="med-insight">
      With prevalence 0.1% and sensitivity 99%, only ~2% of positive tests are
      true positives — the prior dominates.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     VIZ 3 — PROBABILITY TREE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="viz3">Interactive: Probability Tree</h2>

  <p style="color:var(--gd-text-1);margin-bottom:16px;font-size:15px;">
    The tree shows how $P(E)$ sums both branches that produce evidence $E$.
    Branch probabilities update with the Viz 1 sliders.
  </p>

  <div class="gd-chart">
    <div class="gd-chart__title">
      Branch leaf values = P(hypothesis) × P(evidence | hypothesis)
    </div>
    <div id="prob-tree"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     WORKED EXAMPLES
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <h2 id="examples">Worked Examples</h2>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num"
        >Example 1 · Conditional probability + independence check</span
      >
      <p>
        One card is drawn from a 52-card deck. $A$ = "King", $B$ = "Heart". Find
        $P(A \mid B)$. Are $A$ and $B$ independent?
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>
        $P(A) = 4/52 = 1/13$, $P(B) = 13/52 = 1/4$, $P(A \cap B) = 1/52$ (King
        of Hearts).
      </p>
      <p>
        $P(A \mid B) = \dfrac&#123;1/52&#125;&#123;1/4&#125; =
        \dfrac&#123;4&#125;&#123;52&#125; = \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;13&#125;$
      </p>
      <p>
        Independence check: $P(A) \cdot P(B) = \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;13&#125;
        \cdot \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;4&#125; =
        \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;52&#125; = P(A \cap B)$ → <strong
          >independent</strong
        >.
      </p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">
        P(A | B) = 1/13 ≈ 0.077. A and B are independent (being a King and being
        a Heart don't affect each other).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num"
        >Example 2 · Two-event Bayes — GATE 2024 Q58 · NAT · ★★</span
      >
      <p>
        For events $T$ and $S$: $P(\bar&#123;T&#125;) = 0.6$, $P(S \mid T) =
        0.3$, $P(S \mid \bar&#123;T&#125;) = 0.6$. Find $P(T \mid S)$.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Step 1 — Priors:</strong> $P(T) =
        1 - 0.6 = 0.4$, $P(\bar&#123;T&#125;) = 0.6$.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Step 2 — Likelihoods:</strong> $P(S
        \mid T) = 0.3$, $P(S \mid \bar&#123;T&#125;) = 0.6$.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);"
          >Step 3 — Total probability:</strong
        > $P(S) = 0.3 \times 0.4 + 0.6 \times 0.6 = 0.12 + 0.36 = 0.48$.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Step 4 — Bayes:</strong> $P(T \mid
        S) = 0.12 / 0.48 = 0.25$.
      </p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">
        P(T | S) = 0.25. Note the reversal: given P(S|T), we computed P(T|S).
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num"
        >Example 3 · Three-hypothesis Bayes — GATE 2025 Q31 · NAT · ★★</span
      >
      <p>
        Box-1: 2 black, 1 white. Box-2: 1 black, 2 white. Box-3: 3 black, 3
        white. $P(\text&#123;pick Box-1,2,3&#125;) = 1/2, 1/6, 1/3$. A ball
        drawn from the chosen box is white. Find $P(\text&#123;Box-2&#125; \mid
        \text&#123;white&#125;)$.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Priors:</strong> $P(B_1) = 1/2$, $P(B_2)
        = 1/6$, $P(B_3) = 1/3$.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Likelihoods:</strong> $P(W \mid B_1)
        = 1/3$, $P(W \mid B_2) = 2/3$, $P(W \mid B_3) = 1/2$.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Total probability:</strong> $P(W)
        = \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;3&#125;\cdot\dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;2&#125; +
        \dfrac&#123;2&#125;&#123;3&#125;\cdot\dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;6&#125; + \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;2&#125;\cdot\dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;3&#125;
        = \dfrac&#123;3&#125;&#123;18&#125;+\dfrac&#123;2&#125;&#123;18&#125;+\dfrac&#123;3&#125;&#123;18&#125;
        = \dfrac&#123;8&#125;&#123;18&#125; = \dfrac&#123;4&#125;&#123;9&#125;$
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);">Bayes:</strong> $P(B_2 \mid W) = \dfrac&#123;(2/3)(1/6)&#125;&#123;4/9&#125;
        = \dfrac&#123;1/9&#125;&#123;4/9&#125; = \dfrac&#123;1&#125;&#123;4&#125;$
      </p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">
        P(Box-2 | white) = 0.25. Same playbook, 3-way partition.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-example">
    <div class="gd-example__q">
      <span class="gd-example__num"
        >Example 4 · Medical test — GATE 2026 Q57 · NAT · ★★★</span
      >
      <p>
        Disease $D$: sensitivity (true positive rate) = 80%, false positive rate
        = 10%, prevalence = 30%. A person tests positive. Find $P(D \mid +)$.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="gd-example__body">
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--gd-text-0);"
          >Natural-frequency method on 1000 people:</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Have $D$: 300 → positive: $0.80 \times 300 = \mathbf&#123;240&#125;$
        (true positives).
      </p>
      <p>
        No $D$: 700 → positive: $0.10 \times 700 = \mathbf&#123;70&#125;$ (false
        positives).
      </p>
      <p>
        $P(D \mid +) = \dfrac&#123;240&#125;&#123;240 + 70&#125; =
        \dfrac&#123;240&#125;&#123;310&#125; \approx 0.7742$
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--gd-text-2);font-size:14px;">
        Insight: despite 80% sensitivity, the 30% prevalence and 10%
        false-positive rate mean the test isn't overwhelmingly decisive. At 1%
        prevalence with the same test, $P(D \mid +) \approx 0.08$ — the base
        rate dominates.
      </p>
      <div class="gd-example__ans">
        P(D | +) = 0.77. Use the Viz 2 sliders to confirm: sens=0.8, spec=0.9,
        prev=0.3.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     GATE ANGLE
     ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="gd-gate-box">
    <div class="gd-gate-box__title">GATE DA Angle</div>
    <p>
      <strong>Appeared 3 years running:</strong> 2024 Q58, 2025 Q31, 2026 Q57 — all
      2-mark NATs. The form is stable: given priors and likelihoods, compute a posterior.
      The playbook always works.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Reverse-conditional alarm:</strong> if the question gives $P(E \mid
      \text&#123;cause&#125;)$ and asks for $P(\text&#123;cause&#125; \mid E)$, it's
      Bayes. Don't answer with the likelihood — that's the #1 mistake.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Base rate neglect:</strong> when disease is rare, a positive test has
      lower posterior than most people expect. The prior pulls hard on the denominator.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Three-hypothesis Bayes:</strong> identical playbook, just more rows.
      Compute each numerator $P(A \mid B_i)P(B_i)$ then divide by their sum.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Independence check:</strong> verify $P(A \cap B) = P(A)P(B)$ directly
      from the table — never infer independence from "mutually exclusive" (that implies
      the opposite).
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="gd-page-nav">
    <a class="gd-page-nav__item" href="/module1/viz-1-1-counting.html">
      <span class="gd-page-nav__dir">← Previous</span>
      <span class="gd-page-nav__title"
        >1.1 Counting &amp; Basic Probability</span
      >
    </a>
    <a
      class="gd-page-nav__item gd-page-nav__item--next"
      href="/module1/viz-1-3-expectation.html"
    >
      <span class="gd-page-nav__dir">Next →</span>
      <span class="gd-page-nav__title"
        >1.3 Random Variables &amp; Expectation</span
      >
    </a>
  </div>

  <script is:inline slot="scripts">
    // ══════════════════════════════════════════
    // VIZ 1 — BAYES SQUARE
    // ══════════════════════════════════════════
    (function () {
      const W = 480,
        H = 480;
      const svg = d3
        .select("#bayes-square")
        .append("svg")
        .attr("viewBox", `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
        .style("width", "100%")
        .style("max-width", "480px")
        .style("display", "block")
        .style("margin", "0 auto")
        .attr("class", "bayes-square");

      const tooltip = document.getElementById("sq-tooltip");

      let ph = 0.3,
        peh = 0.9,
        penh = 0.2;

      function posterior() {
        const num = peh * ph;
        const denom = peh * ph + penh * (1 - ph);
        return num / denom;
      }

      function pE() {
        return peh * ph + penh * (1 - ph);
      }

      function draw() {
        svg.selectAll("*").remove();

        const pad = 50;
        const iW = W - 2 * pad,
          iH = H - 2 * pad;

        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", pad)
          .attr("y", pad)
          .attr("width", iW)
          .attr("height", iH)
          .attr("fill", "#1e2535")
          .attr("stroke", "#2e3a52");

        const hW = iW * ph;
        const ehH = iH * peh;
        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", pad)
          .attr("y", pad)
          .attr("width", hW)
          .attr("height", ehH)
          .attr("fill", "#7c9eff")
          .attr("opacity", 0.75)
          .on("mouseover", (ev) =>
            showTip(
              ev,
              `P(H ∩ E) = ${(ph * peh).toFixed(3)}\nPosterior numerator`,
            ),
          )
          .on("mouseout", hideTip);

        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", pad)
          .attr("y", pad + ehH)
          .attr("width", hW)
          .attr("height", iH - ehH)
          .attr("fill", "#7c9eff")
          .attr("opacity", 0.2)
          .on("mouseover", (ev) =>
            showTip(ev, `P(H ∩ ¬E) = ${(ph * (1 - peh)).toFixed(3)}`),
          )
          .on("mouseout", hideTip);

        const nhW = iW * (1 - ph);
        const enhH = iH * penh;
        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", pad + hW)
          .attr("y", pad)
          .attr("width", nhW)
          .attr("height", enhH)
          .attr("fill", "#f5c46b")
          .attr("opacity", 0.55)
          .on("mouseover", (ev) =>
            showTip(
              ev,
              `P(¬H ∩ E) = ${((1 - ph) * penh).toFixed(3)}\nFalse positives`,
            ),
          )
          .on("mouseout", hideTip);

        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", pad + hW)
          .attr("y", pad + enhH)
          .attr("width", nhW)
          .attr("height", iH - enhH)
          .attr("fill", "#1e2535")
          .attr("opacity", 1)
          .attr("stroke", "#2e3a52");

        svg
          .append("line")
          .attr("x1", pad + hW)
          .attr("x2", pad + hW)
          .attr("y1", pad)
          .attr("y2", pad + iH)
          .attr("stroke", "#606880")
          .attr("stroke-width", 1.5)
          .attr("stroke-dasharray", "4 3");

        const lc = "#9aa5be",
          fs = 11;
        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad + hW / 2)
          .attr("y", pad - 10)
          .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("fill", "#7c9eff")
          .attr("font-size", fs)
          .attr("font-weight", "600")
          .text(`H (${ph.toFixed(2)})`);
        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad + hW + nhW / 2)
          .attr("y", pad - 10)
          .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("fill", lc)
          .attr("font-size", fs)
          .text(`¬H (${(1 - ph).toFixed(2)})`);
        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad - 8)
          .attr("y", pad + ehH / 2)
          .attr("text-anchor", "end")
          .attr("dominant-baseline", "middle")
          .attr("fill", "#7c9eff")
          .attr("font-size", fs)
          .attr("font-weight", "600")
          .text(`E|H`);
        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad - 8)
          .attr("y", pad + ehH + (iH - ehH) / 2)
          .attr("text-anchor", "end")
          .attr("dominant-baseline", "middle")
          .attr("fill", lc)
          .attr("font-size", fs)
          .text(`¬E|H`);
        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad + hW + nhW / 2)
          .attr("y", pad + enhH + (iH - enhH) / 2 + 4)
          .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("fill", lc)
          .attr("font-size", fs)
          .text(`¬E|¬H`);

        const post = posterior();
        const pe = pE();

        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad + hW / 2)
          .attr("y", pad + ehH / 2)
          .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("dominant-baseline", "middle")
          .attr("fill", "white")
          .attr("font-size", 12)
          .attr("font-weight", "600")
          .text((ph * peh).toFixed(3));

        svg
          .append("text")
          .attr("x", pad + hW + nhW / 2)
          .attr("y", pad + enhH / 2)
          .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
          .attr("dominant-baseline", "middle")
          .attr("fill", "white")
          .attr("font-size", 12)
          .attr("font-weight", "600")
          .text(((1 - ph) * penh).toFixed(3));

        document.getElementById("formula-live-1").innerHTML =
          `P(H|E) = <span class="live-val">${post.toFixed(4)}</span><br>` +
          `= ${(ph * peh).toFixed(3)} / (${(ph * peh).toFixed(3)} + ${((1 - ph) * penh).toFixed(3)})<br>` +
          `= ${(ph * peh).toFixed(3)} / ${pe.toFixed(3)}`;

        document.getElementById("ins-posterior").textContent =
          `Posterior P(H|E) = ${(post * 100).toFixed(1)}%`;
        document.getElementById("ins-pe").textContent =
          `P(E) = P(E|H)·P(H) + P(E|¬H)·P(¬H) = ${pe.toFixed(3)}`;
        document.getElementById("ins-ratio").textContent =
          `Likelihood ratio = P(E|H)/P(E|¬H) = ${(peh / penh).toFixed(2)}`;
      }

      function showTip(ev, text) {
        const rect = document
          .getElementById("bayes-square")
          .getBoundingClientRect();
        tooltip.innerHTML = text.replace(/\n/g, "<br>");
        tooltip.classList.add("gd-tooltip--visible");
        tooltip.style.left = ev.clientX - rect.left + 12 + "px";
        tooltip.style.top = ev.clientY - rect.top - 30 + "px";
      }
      function hideTip() {
        tooltip.classList.remove("gd-tooltip--visible");
      }

      function bindSliders() {
        [
          ["ph", (v) => (ph = v), "ph-val", (v) => v.toFixed(2)],
          ["peh", (v) => (peh = v), "peh-val", (v) => v.toFixed(2)],
          ["penh", (v) => (penh = v), "penh-val", (v) => v.toFixed(2)],
        ].forEach(([id, set, valId, fmt]) => {
          document.getElementById(id).addEventListener("input", function () {
            set(+this.value);
            document.getElementById(valId).textContent = fmt(+this.value);
            draw();
            updateTree();
          });
        });
      }

      draw();
      bindSliders();
      window._bayesParams = () => ({ ph, peh, penh });

      // ── VIZ 3 — PROBABILITY TREE (uses Viz 1 sliders) ──
      function updateTree() {
        const { ph, peh, penh } = window._bayesParams();
        const tW = 560,
          tH = 300;
        const svg = d3.select("#prob-tree");
        svg.selectAll("*").remove();

        const s = svg
          .append("svg")
          .attr("viewBox", `0 0 ${tW} ${tH}`)
          .style("width", "100%")
          .style("max-width", `${tW}px`)
          .style("display", "block")
          .style("margin", "0 auto");

        const g = s.append("g").attr("transform", "translate(20,20)");

        const root = { x: 60, y: 130 };
        const nH = { x: 220, y: 60 };
        const nnH = { x: 220, y: 200 };
        const nHE = { x: 400, y: 30 };
        const nHnE = { x: 400, y: 90 };
        const nnHE = { x: 400, y: 170 };
        const nnHnE = { x: 400, y: 230 };

        [
          [root, nH],
          [root, nnH],
          [nH, nHE],
          [nH, nHnE],
          [nnH, nnHE],
          [nnH, nnHnE],
        ].forEach(([a, b]) => {
          g.append("path")
            .attr("class", "tree-link")
            .attr(
              "d",
              `M${a.x},${a.y} C${(a.x + b.x) / 2},${a.y} ${(a.x + b.x) / 2},${b.y} ${b.x},${b.y}`,
            );
        });

        function node(pos, label, sublabel, color, isE) {
          const ng = g
            .append("g")
            .attr("transform", `translate(${pos.x},${pos.y})`);
          ng.append("circle")
            .attr("r", 16)
            .attr("fill", color)
            .attr("stroke", isE ? "#7c9eff" : "#2e3a52")
            .attr("stroke-width", isE ? 2 : 1);
          ng.append("text")
            .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
            .attr("dominant-baseline", "middle")
            .attr("fill", "white")
            .attr("font-size", 9)
            .attr("font-weight", "600")
            .text(label);
          g.append("text")
            .attr("x", pos.x + (pos.x > 250 ? 24 : -24))
            .attr("y", pos.y - 4)
            .attr("text-anchor", pos.x > 250 ? "start" : "end")
            .attr("fill", "#9aa5be")
            .attr("font-size", 10)
            .text(sublabel);
        }

        const blue = "#7c9eff",
          amber = "#f5c46b",
          muted = "#252d40";
        node(root, "start", "", "#2e3a52", false);
        node(nH, "H", `p=${ph.toFixed(2)}`, blue, false);
        node(nnH, "¬H", `p=${(1 - ph).toFixed(2)}`, muted, false);
        node(nHE, "E", `${(ph * peh).toFixed(3)}`, blue, true);
        node(nHnE, "¬E", `${(ph * (1 - peh)).toFixed(3)}`, muted, false);
        node(nnHE, "E", `${((1 - ph) * penh).toFixed(3)}`, amber, true);
        node(
          nnHnE,
          "¬E",
          `${((1 - ph) * (1 - penh)).toFixed(3)}`,
          muted,
          false,
        );

        function branchLabel(a, b, txt) {
          g.append("text")
            .attr("x", (a.x + b.x) / 2 - 6)
            .attr("y", (a.y + b.y) / 2 - 6)
            .attr("text-anchor", "end")
            .attr("fill", "#606880")
            .attr("font-size", 10)
            .text(txt);
        }
        branchLabel(root, nH, `P(H)=${ph.toFixed(2)}`);
        branchLabel(root, nnH, `P(¬H)=${(1 - ph).toFixed(2)}`);
        branchLabel(nH, nHE, `P(E|H)=${peh.toFixed(2)}`);
        branchLabel(nH, nHnE, `P(¬E|H)=${(1 - peh).toFixed(2)}`);
        branchLabel(nnH, nnHE, `P(E|¬H)=${penh.toFixed(2)}`);
        branchLabel(nnH, nnHnE, `P(¬E|¬H)=${(1 - penh).toFixed(2)}`);

        const pe = peh * ph + penh * (1 - ph);
        const post = (peh * ph) / pe;
        g.append("text")
          .attr("x", 530)
          .attr("y", 100)
          .attr("text-anchor", "end")
          .attr("fill", "#7c9eff")
          .attr("font-size", 11)
          .attr("font-weight", "600")
          .text(`P(E) = ${pe.toFixed(3)}`);
        g.append("text")
          .attr("x", 530)
          .attr("y", 118)
          .attr("text-anchor", "end")
          .attr("fill", "#9aa5be")
          .attr("font-size", 10)
          .text(`P(H|E) = ${post.toFixed(3)}`);
      }

      window.updateTree = updateTree;
      updateTree();
    })();

    // ══════════════════════════════════════════
    // VIZ 2 — MEDICAL TEST
    // ══════════════════════════════════════════
    (function () {
      const N = 10000;
      let prevalence = 0.001,
        sensitivity = 0.99,
        specificity = 0.95;

      const fmtPct = (v) =>
        (v * 100).toFixed(v < 0.01 ? 1 : v < 0.1 ? 1 : 0) + "%";

      function updateMedical() {
        const disease = Math.round(N * prevalence);
        const noDisease = N - disease;
        const tp = Math.round(disease * sensitivity);
        const fp = Math.round(noDisease * (1 - specificity));
        const totalPos = tp + fp;
        const post = totalPos > 0 ? tp / totalPos : 0;

        document.getElementById("med-tp").textContent = tp.toLocaleString();
        document.getElementById("med-fp").textContent = fp.toLocaleString();
        document.getElementById("med-total-pos").textContent =
          totalPos.toLocaleString();
        document.getElementById("med-posterior").textContent = fmtPct(post);

        const container = document.getElementById("medical-bars");
        const cW = container.clientWidth || 500;
        const cH = 120;
        d3.select(container).select("svg").remove();
        const svg = d3
          .select(container)
          .append("svg")
          .attr("viewBox", `0 0 ${cW} ${cH}`)
          .style("width", "100%")
          .style("display", "block");

        const barH = 44,
          barY = 10;
        const scale = d3
          .scaleLinear()
          .domain([0, N])
          .range([0, cW - 60]);

        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", 30)
          .attr("y", barY)
          .attr("width", scale(N))
          .attr("height", barH)
          .attr("fill", "#1e2535")
          .attr("rx", 4);
        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", 30)
          .attr("y", barY)
          .attr("width", scale(disease))
          .attr("height", barH)
          .attr("fill", "#e05c6b")
          .attr("opacity", 0.4)
          .attr("rx", 4);
        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", 30)
          .attr("y", barY)
          .attr("width", scale(tp))
          .attr("height", barH)
          .attr("fill", "#6ee7a8")
          .attr("opacity", 0.8)
          .attr("rx", 4);
        svg
          .append("rect")
          .attr("x", 30 + scale(disease))
          .attr("y", barY)
          .attr("width", scale(fp))
          .attr("height", barH)
          .attr("fill", "#f5c46b")
          .attr("opacity", 0.7)
          .attr("rx", 4);

        [
          [0, "#6ee7a8", "TP", tp],
          [scale(disease), "#f5c46b", "FP", fp],
        ].forEach(([x, c, lbl, v]) => {
          if (scale(v) > 20) {
            svg
              .append("text")
              .attr("x", 30 + x + scale(v) / 2)
              .attr("y", barY + barH / 2 + 4)
              .attr("text-anchor", "middle")
              .attr("fill", "white")
              .attr("font-size", 11)
              .attr("font-weight", "600")
              .text(lbl);
          }
        });

        [
          ["#6ee7a8", "True Positive"],
          ["#f5c46b", "False Positive"],
          ["#e05c6b", "Has disease (all)"],
        ].forEach(([c, l], i) => {
          const lx = 30 + i * 160;
          svg
            .append("rect")
            .attr("x", lx)
            .attr("y", barY + barH + 12)
            .attr("width", 10)
            .attr("height", 10)
            .attr("fill", c)
            .attr("rx", 2);
          svg
            .append("text")
            .attr("x", lx + 14)
            .attr("y", barY + barH + 20)
            .attr("fill", "#9aa5be")
            .attr("font-size", 10)
            .text(l);
        });

        const iEl = document.getElementById("med-insight");
        if (post < 0.1) {
          iEl.textContent = `⚠ Even with ${fmtPct(sensitivity)} sensitivity, only ${fmtPct(post)} of positive tests are real — because the disease affects only ${fmtPct(prevalence)} of the population. Base rate dominates!`;
          iEl.className = "gd-insight gd-insight--warn";
        } else {
          iEl.textContent = `With prevalence ${fmtPct(prevalence)}, P(Disease|Test+) = ${fmtPct(post)}. As prevalence rises, the posterior improves significantly.`;
          iEl.className = "gd-insight gd-insight--insight";
        }
      }

      [
        [
          "prevalence",
          (v) => {
            prevalence = v;
            document.getElementById("prev-val").textContent =
              (v * 100).toFixed(v < 0.01 ? 2 : 1) + "%";
          },
        ],
        [
          "sensitivity",
          (v) => {
            sensitivity = v;
            document.getElementById("sens-val").textContent = v.toFixed(2);
          },
        ],
        [
          "specificity",
          (v) => {
            specificity = v;
            document.getElementById("spec-val").textContent = v.toFixed(2);
          },
        ],
      ].forEach(([id, set]) => {
        document.getElementById(id).addEventListener("input", function () {
          set(+this.value);
          updateMedical();
        });
      });

      updateMedical();
    })();
  </script>
</VizLayout>
